COMPARISON (paraphrase obey/recall):
  deployed Jaccard selector (SP_RECALL_JACCARD): ~8.2%   (lexical; collapses on paraphrase)
  SP_RECALL_L5 (this):                            86.89%  (directional L5 query-key cosine)
  offline prediction (G-REP-LAYER-L5, cosine recall@1): 88.5%  -> live 86.89% is within noise.

The 7 LEAK + 1 OTHER are the hard cases where the planted counter-fact loses to unshakeable
parametric knowledge (sun_star "Sun is a star", mona_country "Louvre/Paris", everest_country "Asia",
olympics_years "every four years", photosynth "CO2") or the model abstained (water_formula
"I don't know" = OTHER, a safe non-leak).

COMBINER NOTE (rep_combine.py, offline): a gated (Jaccard-else-L5) or learned-logistic head over
[Jaccard, L5, KSTE-MD] does NOT beat L5 alone — L5 already covers 100% exact AND ~88% paraphrase, so
the other signals are redundant (Jaccard) or dead on this directional axis (KSTE-MD magnitude-shape,
learned weight ~0.14, MD-only para=0%). The multi-signal head's remaining value is foreign-reject /
abstention calibration (untested — no foreign queries in this corpus), not recall@1.

VERDICT: GREEN-LIVE. L5 query-key cosine recall is the deployable paraphrase-robust selector on the
served 12B (86.89% para obey vs Jaccard 8%), default-off, byte-identical null floor when unset.
